cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

The paper deals with optical flow estimation, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a new network architecture for estimating uncertainty. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses supervised learning and neural networks, which are relevant to sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Winner-Takes-All loss and multi-hypotheses networks is related to sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.RO (Robotics).
